>IAssemblySymbol.TypeNames

It returns strings with simple type name ðŸ˜• - we need full qualify type names.

```c#
$guid = [Guid]::NewGuid().ToString().Replace("-","")

$CSharpCode1 = @"
        namespace Test.AddType1
        {
            public class CSharpTest1$guid
            {
                public static int Add1(int a, int b)
                {
                    return (a + b);
                }
            }
            public class CSharpTest2$guid
            {
                public static int Add2(int a, int b)
                {
                    return (a + b);
                }
            }
        }
        namespace Test.AddType2
        {
            public class CSharpTest1$guid
            {
                public static int Add1(int a, int b)
                {
                    return (a + b);
                }
            }
            public class CSharpTest2$guid
            {
                public static int Add2(int a, int b)
                {
                    return (a + b);
                }
            }
        }
"@

Add-Type -TypeDefinition $CSharpCode1
```
